text.section:
"Eligible individual" means an individual who:
is a resident of Maryland;
is a Medicare beneficiary enrolled in the Medicare Part D Voluntary Prescription Drug Benefit Program or a Medicare Advantage Plan that provides Part D coverage;
is not enrolled in a health benefit plan, other than a Medicare Part D prescription drug plan or a Medicare Advantage Plan, that provides prescription drug benefits at the time that the individual applies for enrollment in the Program;
has an annual household income at or below 300% of the federal poverty guidelines;
is not eligible for a full federal low-income subsidy under 42 C.F.R. § 423.772; and
pays the premium, and copayments or coinsurance, for the Program.
